The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 DBS to buy 37% of Chola

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 Mumbai, June 16: The Singapores DBS Bank will pick up a 37.5 per cent stake in Chennai-based Cholamandalam Investment and Finance Company (CIFCL) in a deal worth Rs 228 crore.

 Cholamandalam Investment and Finance is a Murugappa group company.

 DBS and the Murugappa group will be equal stakeholders in CIFCL after the deal, CIFCL chairman M. A. Alagappan said after signing the agreement with Jackson Tai, vice-chairman and CEO of DBS Group Holdings.

 According to the agreement, the Murugappa group, which owns 55 per cent stake in CIFCL through Tube Investments of India, will offload 15.1 per cent stake to DBS Bank. The Singapore bank will also come out with an offer to buy another 20 per cent from the public.

 The remaining stake would come from a preferential share issue by CIFCL to DBS. The entire transaction is subject to regulatory and shareholder approval. 

 CIFCL will be renamed Cholamandalam DBS Finance Limited. 




